<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 9:22PM CDT  by NWS Central Illinois</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL FULTON...
SOUTHWESTERN TAZEWELL...NORTHEASTERN MASON AND SOUTH CENTRAL PEORIA
COUNTIES THROUGH 945 PM CDT...
At 921 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of St. David, or 8 miles southeast of Canton, moving east
at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pekin, Manito, South Pekin, Glasford, Kingston Mines, Mapleton,
Forest City, Banner, and Powerton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
